        public static void assertEqualModelItems(ModelItem actual,
                                         ModelItem expected)
        Asserts that two ModelItems have the same values for all their attributes except the excluded ones. The serialization strategy of the expected ModelItems is used for this assertion.
        Parameters:
        actual - the actual ModelItem
        expected - the expected ModelItem

      • assertEqualModelItems

        public static void assertEqualModelItems(ModelItem actual,
                                         ModelItem expected,
                                         SerializationStrategy tempStrategy)
        Asserts that two ModelItems have the same values for all their attributes except the excluded ones. If the serialization strategy is not null, the serialization strategy of the ModelItems is replaced for this assertion, but restored afterwards.
        Parameters:
        actual - the actual ModelItem
        expected - the expected ModelItem
        tempStrategy - the (temporary) serialization strategy

      • assertEqualModelItemsNoOrder

        public static void assertEqualModelItemsNoOrder(List<? extends ModelItem> actual,
                                                List<? extends ModelItem> expected)
        Asserts that two lists of ModelItems contain the same elements, thus are equal ignoring the order. Uses the SerializationStrategy of each item in expected.
        Parameters:
        actual - list one
        expected - list two

      • assertEqualModelItemsNoOrder

        public static void assertEqualModelItemsNoOrder(List<? extends ModelItem> actual,
                                                List<? extends ModelItem> expected,
                                                SerializationStrategy tempStrategy)
        Asserts that two lists of ModelItems contain the same elements, thus are equal ignoring the order. It is possible to supply a custom exclusion strategy, otherwise the serialization strategy of the expected items are used. For lists containing different types of ModelItems, it is recommended to set the appropriate serialization strategies beforehand and simply pass null or to simply use assertEqualModelItemsNoOrder(List, List).
        Parameters:
        actual - list one
        expected - list two
        tempStrategy - the (temporary) serialization strategy

      • assertEqualModelItemsNoOrder

        public static void assertEqualModelItemsNoOrder(List<? extends ModelItem> actual,
                                                List<? extends ModelItem> expected,
                                                SerializationStrategy tempStrategy,
                                                boolean equalItems)
        Asserts that two lists of ModelItems contain the same elements, thus are equal ignoring the order. It is possible to supply a custom exclusion strategy, otherwise the serialization strategy of the expected items are used. For lists containing different types of ModelItems, it is recommended to set the appropriate serialization strategies beforehand and simply pass null or to simply use assertEqualModelItemsNoOrder(List, List).
        Parameters:
        actual - list one
        expected - list two
        tempStrategy - the (temporary) serialization strategy
        equalItems - if false, the items must not be equal
